            <title>[HBASE-1666] &apos;safe mode&apos; is broken; MetaScanner initial scan completes without scanning .META.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1666</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;initial scan completed flag is set on scanner though it hasn&apos;t been deployed never mind scanned.  This means we pass out of safe mode soon after startup.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Even if metascanner is fixed so initialScan does not complete till after .META. has been scanned the first time, &apos;safe mode&apos; seems to mess with region assignment in a way that makes it crawl.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Investigate and fix.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
